 of accreted H and a low-activity Sun,\nbecause in other cases too much CO$_2$ is lost during evolution, which is\ninconsistent with Venus' present atmosphere. Important issues are likely the\ntime at which the initial steam atmosphere is outgassed and/or the amount of\nCO$_2$ which may still be delivered at later evolutionary stages. A late\naccretion scenario can only reproduce present isotope ratios for a highly\nactive young Sun, but then very massive steam atmospheres would be required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jun 2017 16:21:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 Oct 2017 11:12:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-30"}
