{"id":"1706.07127","submitter":"Andrey Sarantsev Mr","authors":"Tomoyuki Ichiba, Andrey Sarantsev","title":"Convergence and Stationary Distributions for Walsh Diffusions","comments":"30 pages. Keywords: Walsh Brownian motion, Walsh diffusion,\n  stochastic differential equation, stationary distribution, invariant measure,\n  ergodic process, Lyapunov function, reflected diffusion","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A Walsh diffusion on Euclidean space moves along each ray from the origin, as\na solution to a stochastic differential equation with certain drift and\ndiffusion coefficients, as long as it stays away from the origin. As it hits\nthe origin, it instantaneously chooses a new direction according to a given\nprobability law, called the spinning measure. A special example is a\nreal-valued diffusion with skew reflections at the origin. This process\ncontinuously (in the weak sense) depends on the spinning measure. We determine\na stationary measure for such process, explore long-term convergence to this\ndistribution and establish an explicit rate of exponential convergence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jun 2017 21:58:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 14 Apr 2018 20:45:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 29 Jun 2018 04:48:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-02"}
